The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, December 07, 2002 				Metro Recommends
				 																The Book				 																																	(Christopher Kremmer)				 																																	lA truthful and straightforward account of the authors travels through Afghanistan, Pakistan and Kashmir. The good, bad and ugly of this frontier region is portrayed through the lives of those involved in the carpet trade. The journey across the Islamic heartlands fills the rug with religious and political significance				 																The soiree				 																																	(Emami Landmark Store, December 10, 6.30 pm)				 																																	lSinger Anjan Dutta will sing 10 ballads from his latest album, based on contemporary issues. The songs will be interspersed with English poems by Sharmila Ray. A lyrical commentary of our times				 																The Show				 																																	(Taj Bengal, December 7, 6.30 pm)				 																																	lThe annual fashion show of the Institute of Fashion amp; Techno Art, Bhawanipur Gujarati Education Society will feature ensembles created by the students. To be attended by the glitterati and representatives from the industry				 																The Album				 																																	(Mahalakshmi Iyer)				 																																	lThe queen of commercial jingles debuts with her first solo Hindi album that scales the heights. Watch out for Zindagi and Mast Mast that have been scored by Shankar Mahadevan and Instant Karma
